PARAKEET-TRANSCRIBE
===================

Fast speech-to-text transcription using NVIDIA Parakeet models via ONNX Runtime.

COMMANDS
--------

  transcribe <audio.wav>
      Simple transcription (TDT model, multilingual)

  transcribe-daemon [model_dir]
      Start daemon with preloaded model for fast repeated transcriptions
      Default model_dir: /usr/share/parakeet-transcribe/tdt

  transcribe-client <audio.wav>
      Send audio to daemon for transcription (requires transcribe-daemon running)

  transcribe-diarize <audio.wav>
      Transcription with speaker identification (TDT + Sortformer)

  transcribe-stream-diarize [audio.wav]
      Streaming transcription with diarization (Nemotron + Sortformer, English only)
      Without argument: records from microphone (Ctrl+C to stop)

  dictee
      Push-to-talk dictation script for desktop use
      First call: starts recording
      Second call: stops, transcribes, and types text via ydotool

MODELS
------

Models are stored in /usr/share/parakeet-transcribe/

  tdt/          - Parakeet TDT (multilingual, 25 languages)
  sortformer/   - Sortformer v2.1 (speaker diarization, up to 4 speakers)
  nemotron/     - Nemotron (streaming English with punctuation)

SYSTEMD SERVICE
---------------

Enable the daemon for fast transcription:

  systemctl --user daemon-reload
  systemctl --user enable --now parakeet-transcribe

CONFIGURATION
-------------

For dictee with animation, edit /usr/bin/dictee and set:

  BIN_PATH="/path/to/animation-speech/directory"
  ANIMATION_CONFIG="circular"
  ANIMATION_PARAM="-p center -w 1000 -H 150"

DEPENDENCIES
------------

  - ydotool (for dictee)
  - pipewire or pulseaudio-utils or alsa-utils (for recording)
  - curl (for model download)

